A ternary conditional in JavaScript is a conditional that has only one if and else statement.

Example:

if(conditional){
  doThis();
}else{
  doThat();
}

you can reduce the code using ternary conditional:

@ conditional ? doThis() : doThat();

------------------------------------------------

Example:

function logHello(){
  console.log('Hello');
}
function logWorld(){
  console.log('World');
}
let a = 2;
a == 5 ? logHello() : logWorld();

>>> 'World'
